    "Management": {
      "text": "Remove extrinsic factors and/or pacemakers\nPacemakers do not reduce mortality, only decrease symptoms\nConsider reversible causes e.g. treat\nhyperkalemia\nor\nhypokalemia\nAtropine\nfor bradycardia, progress to catecholamine or pacing\nconsider\naminophylline\n, which inhibits suppressive effects of adenosine on the SA node in:\n[2]\nAcute inferior\nMI\nwith 2nd or 3rd degree AV block; 250mv IV bolus\nHeart transplant: 6mg/kg in 100-200mL of IV fluid over 20-30 minutes\nSpinal cord injury: 6mg/kg in 100-200mL of IV fluid over 20-30 minutes",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
